Kiess's interest in the Great Pyramid is primarily as a downstream commercial variable: pyramid-origin materials pass through the Eastern Desert and Saltglass Reach trade chains before reaching Kiess markets, and the Synod's presence in the pyramid complex is a factor in those chains' reliability. The Temple of Concord preserves fragments of Keeper-of-Measure survey prayers using astronomical vocabulary cognate to the Solar Court's celestial-governance doctrine — both descend from the same continental tradition of astronomical-administrative fusion. Kiess has no direct presence in the pyramid zone.

