Ushabti relationship to the Great Pyramid is primary and foundational: the Solar Court's administrative tradition — tribute accounting, soul adjudication, legal memory maintenance — is the origin institution of the administrative practice Ushabti carry as cultural identity. The Black Sun Shard containment is preserved in Ushabti legal memory as the founding justification for the entire Solar Court apparatus. This distinguishes Ushabti reading from outsider reading: Ushabti do not see a monumental tomb with secondary administrative functions but an administrative containment system with monumental camouflage. The Correction sentence class is the institutional crime Ushabti legal tradition most specifically condemns: not merely injustice but the weaponization of the record system against the people it was built to protect. Ushabti in Midgaard are the most reliable source of Correction-class artifact identification because their cultural memory includes the specific inscription patterns the Jackal Tribunal used to mark altered testimony.

